    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1967-06-21T17:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1967-06-21T17:30:00-05:00" n="313"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <head>313. Notes of Meeting of the Special Committee of the National Security
                        Council<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d313fn1">Source: <persName
                            corresp="#p_JLB1">Johnson</persName> Library, National Security File,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Special Committee Files, Minutes and
                        Notes. No classification marking. The meeting was held in the Cabinet Room
                        at the White House. Notes are the handwritten notes of <persName
                            corresp="#p_SHH1">Harold H. Saunders</persName>. The President joined
                        the meeting from 6:50 p.m. until 7:06 p.m. (Ibid., President’s Daily Diary)
                            <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">Bundy</persName>’s memorandum for the
                        record, June 21, states: “1. The President agreed to see King <persName
                            corresp="#p_HIT1">Hussein</persName> if he comes to the United Nations.
                        2. The President agreed that we should let it be known quietly that we do
                        not consider General <persName corresp="#p_DGC1">De Gaulle</persName> an
                        acceptable mediator of a Mid-East solution.” (Ibid., National Security File,
                            <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Special Committee Files, Minutes and
                        Notes)</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1967-06-21T18:30:00-04:00">June 21, 1967, 6:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="participants">
                    <head>THOSE PRESENT</head>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_KNB1">Katzenbach</persName>, Acting Secretary of
                        State</item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WGEG1">Wheeler</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HRM1">Helms</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CCM1">Clifford</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_RWW1">W.W. Rostow</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BMG1">McG. Bundy</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VCR1">Vance</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_REV1">E.V. Rostow</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BLD1">Battle</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MPHCJ1">Harry McPherson</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHH1">Harold Saunders</persName>
                    </item>
                    <item>[<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>], <gloss target="#t_CIA1"
                            >CIA</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>The President came in at 6:50 p.m.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="#p_CG1">George Christian</persName> came in at 6:55 p.m.</p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">1. Informal discussion:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_UAR1">UAR</gloss> trying to buy food for cash. Russian wheat
                    problem. <persName corresp="#p_KNB1">Katzenbach</persName> sees no objection.
                    Cargill—$10 m.—<gloss target="#t_UAR1">UAR</gloss> has asked to buy.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d313fn2">The following appears at this point in <persName
                            corresp="#p_SHH1">Saunders</persName>’ notes in a box, apparently added
                        later in the discussion: “President said: ‘I’m going to be easily raped by
                        anyone who wants to pay cash. I’ve been giving it away for so long…
                        .’”</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">2. Emergency relief:</hi>
                    <list>
                        <item>—Swedish appeal in <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>.</item>
                        <item>—What can we do now to avoid permanent commitment to status
                            quo.</item>
                        <item>—Responsibility to those holding political authority.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>EVR: Work through UNWRA.</p>
                <pb facs="0563" n="531" xml:id="pg_531"/>
                <p>—WWR: Regional increment 60%.</p>
                <p>—<persName corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName>: We shouldn’t put up 70%. Put
                    it on regional basis.</p>
                <p>—McGB summary: <list>
                        <item>—Less than 70%</item>
                        <item>—Regional response</item>
                        <item>—Not get out in front</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>—<persName corresp="#p_BLD1">Battle</persName>: decrease share</p>
                <p>—Refer back to Dept. for a framework in which our contribution would be well
                    down.</p>
                <list>
                    <item>—Outside vs. regional contribution</item>
                    <item>—US vs. US [<hi rend="italic">
                            <gloss target="#t_USSR1">USSR</gloss>
                        </hi>?] non-regional</item>
                    <item>—Short-term nature of commitment</item>
                </list>
                <p>Plus soundings on the Hill.</p>
                <p>McGB: Signal Israelis?<note n="3" xml:id="d313fn3">In a statement released on
                        June 27, the President announced that the United States would join with
                        other nations in a special effort to provide emergency assistance in the
                        Middle East and announced the establishment of a reserve of $5 million from
                        contingency funds for this purpose. He stated that he had directed U.S.
                        participation in the appropriate <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> emergency
                        programs of food and medical relief and that the U.S. Government was
                        offering $100,000 for use by the International Red Cross to assist victims
                        of the conflict. (Public Papers of the Presidents of the United States:
                            <persName corresp="#p_JLB1">Lyndon B. Johnson</persName>, 1967, Book I,
                        p. 660)</note>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">3. Military:</hi>
                    <list>
                        <item>Go over paper<note n="4" xml:id="d313fn4">Not further
                                identified.</note> at next meeting</item>
                        <item>McN: Against Libya.<note n="5" xml:id="d313fn5">
                                <persName corresp="#p_HRM1">Helms</persName>’ notes of the meeting
                                say on this point: “<gloss target="#t_DOD1">DOD</gloss> opposed to
                                arms shipments for Libya—OK on Morocco and <persName
                                    corresp="#p_JCAAJ1">Jordan</persName>.” (Central Intelligence
                                Agency Files, <gloss target="#t_DCI1">DCI</gloss> Files: Job
                                80–B1285A, Box 11, Folder 12, <gloss target="#t_DCI1">DCI</gloss>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_HRM1">Helms</persName>) Miscellaneous
                                Notes of Meetings, 1 Jan 1966–31 Dec 1968)</note>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">4. Egyptians &amp; French:</hi>
                    <list>
                        <item>—Not something we need to rush in on.</item>
                        <item>—Get it around that <persName corresp="#p_DGC1">De Gaulle</persName>
                            not going to be our mediator.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">5. <persName corresp="#p_JCAAJ1">Jordan</persName>:</hi>
                    <list>
                        <item>—<persName corresp="#p_HIT1">Hussein</persName>. <gloss
                                target="#t_LBJ1">LBJ</gloss> wld. see.</item>
                        <item>—On Am. TV.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <hi rend="italic">General policy guideline:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Moderate the moderates.</p>
            </div>
